    "And following equation 3, when both the evaluator and information transparency entered the regression equation, the evaluator could not significantly predict the perception of fairness (p > 0.05), whereas information transparency significantly predicted the perception of fairness (β = 0.41, SE = 0.07, p < 0.001).",
    "Therefore, information transparency played a full mediating effect between the evaluator and the perception of fairness, with the mediating effect accounting for 49.05% of the total effect (See Figure 4).",
